# Manifest CSV — one row per PDF.
#
# The manifest is the single source of truth for the pipeline. Build it
# programmatically from the source directory (see scripts/inventory_builder.py)
# rather than by hand. Regenerate it with ALICE paths before deployment
# (scripts/alice_deploy.sh).
#
# Required columns:
#   pdf_id          Unique identifier. Convention: <series>_<lang>_<chapter>.
#   language        Lowercase label matching the PROMPTS dict in prompts.py
#                   (e.g. "korean", "polish", "english").
#   filename        Original PDF filename (basename only, no directory).
#   pdf_path        Absolute path to the PDF. Local on the student's machine
#                   before deployment; /zfsstore/... after rewriting for ALICE.
#   total_pages     Page count (from PyMuPDF).
#   content_start   0-indexed page where content begins, inclusive (skips
#                   title pages, Naver navigation UI on page 0 of Korean
#                   webtoon PDFs, etc.).
#   content_end     0-indexed page where content ends, inclusive (skips
#                   comments section, blank back-matter). Page range to
#                   process is content_start..content_end (both included).
#
# Optional columns (add when relevant to analysis):
#   series          Grouping key for multi-document collections.
#   series_title    Human-readable title for display.
#   chapter         Sequential number within the series.
#   date / year     Temporal analysis.
#   subject         Topic/domain label for mixed-domain corpora.
#   level           Education level, etc.
#
# CSV readers should skip lines starting with '#'. In pandas:
#   pd.read_csv('manifest.csv', comment='#')
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
pdf_id,series,series_title,language,chapter,filename,pdf_path,total_pages,content_start,content_end
